Welcome to OffTopicGC! We own several sites, so we have setup some rules for all of them.<br><br>By using any of our sites "projects", you are agreeing to these terms. You also agree that if you break any of these terms, you will be removed from our sites.<br><br>If we say "OffTopicGC", "OTGC", "us", "we", and "our", we mean OTGC. If we say "you", and "your", we're talking about <strong>you</strong>.<br><br>If you feel like someone is breaking these terms, or if you have been removed from any of our projects, you may attempt to appeal at <a href="https://discord.com/invite/MPMXmCNbE9" target="_blank">the Support server</a>.<hr><h3>1. Who are we?</h3><p>OTGC is a group chat on <a href="https://discord.com" target="_blank">Discord</a>, where we use source codes we find interesting, and fork those source codes and additionally fix them.<h3>2. Age Requirement</h3><p>To access any of our projects, you agree to being over 13 "thirteen" years old and meet the minimum age of digital consent in your country. If you do not meet this requirement, you will be removed from our projects, and may appeal when you are old enough to use our projects again.</p><h3>3. Projects</h3><p>All of our projects are not written by us. It is considered forks, with more features and bug fixes. If we are using one of your projects, you may create a ticket in the support server to have the project removed.<!--brickhill is an exception lol--></p><h3>4. Content you post</h3><p>The content you post must NOT include the following:</p><ul><li>NSFW/NSFL</li><li>Gore</li><li>Cropped Content</li></ul><p>If you post any of these, you will be immediately removed from the targeted project/Discord server.</p><hr>Please be aware of what you do on OTGC. The Terms is not finished being written. <strong>Any loopholes will receive a strike</strong>.
